&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for enthusiastic, motivated and committed individuals to join our friendly and dynamic team within the Trauma and Orthopaedics Department at East Suffolk and North Essex NHS Foundation Trust. It is an exciting time in our development as a merged trust and departments becoming one of the largest Orthopaedic departments in the country.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary of offer &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One 10 PA (minimum) contract for Trauma and Orthopaedic surgeons with specific interest in upper limb elective and trauma reconstructive surgery The post will be based Colchester Hospital and be part of the on call trauma rotas. Elective care will at the Colchester Hospital and a planned purpose built elective orthopaedic centre. Working at any ESNEFT site may be required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MB ChB or equivalentFull GMC Registration&lt;br /&gt;FRCS Orth &lt;br /&gt;Specialist accreditation or within 6 months of attaining CCT.&lt;br /&gt;ATLS&lt;br /&gt;Post CCT Fellowship trained in upper limb surgery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contact details for discussion about the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mr Mark Bowditch (Divisional Director MSK &amp; Special Surgery)&lt;br /&gt;Mr Mark Loeffler (Clinical Director MSK) &lt;br /&gt;Mr Matt Hynes (Clinical Lead T&amp;O, Colchester site)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Colchester Switchboard 01206 747474 or Ipswich Switchboard 01473 712233&lt;/p&gt;
